HEADWORD: Reflet
<hw>Re*flet"</hw> <pr>(r⟦eit⟧*fl⟦ecr⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F., reflection. See <er>Reflect</er>.]</ety> <def>Luster; special
brilliancy of surface; -- used esp. in ceramics to denote the peculiar
metallic brilliancy seen in lustered pottery such as majolica; <as>as,
silver <ex>reflet</ex>; gold <ex>reflet</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

